LONGVIEW POWER, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Longview Power, LLC ( Longview ) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ( Reactive Supply Service ) from the Longview generating facility located in Maidsville, West Virginia and interconnected to the West Penn Power Company (d/b/a Allegheny Power) ( West Penn ) transmission system, which is under the operational control of PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ( PJM ). This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Longview s revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from Longview s generation facility to PJM and West Penn.
This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The total Reactive Service Annual Revenue Requirement is $685,000.08, and the total monthly charge is $57,083.34.
